Dialogue: 10,0:00:14.30,0:00:16.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Eight hundred years ago,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:17.20,0:00:21.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Heike and Genji clans fought the final battle
Dialogue: 10,0:00:21.58,0:00:26.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of their long-standing feud at Dan-no-Ura, \Nin the waters of the Kanmon Straits. {https://maps.app.goo.gl/GPjibGsQ24U7aRj17}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:30.54,0:00:34.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Although the Genji had more ships,\N they were initially
Dialogue: 10,0:00:34.96,0:00:39.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,at a disadvantage against the Heike,\Nwho were more skilled in sea battles.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:39.02,0:00:42.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Still, with the power of their determination,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.48,0:00:46.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,they pushed the Heike westward against the shore.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:47.18,0:00:50.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then the samurai of Shikoku and Kyushu defected to the Genji side.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:50.68,0:00:54.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Heike were trapped, \Nwith nowhere to escape.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:08.57,0:01:12.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Heike clan, once so proud \Nof its military glory,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:12.48,0:01:17.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was completely wiped out \Nand met a bitter end at Dan-no-Ura.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.62,0:02:19.79,Song,,0,0,0,,The bell of the Gion temple
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.34,0:02:37.53,Song,,0,0,0,,Tells of the vanity of worldly things
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.68,0:02:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi-san!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.96,0:02:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here! I'm over here. {talks in 3rd person for some reason, maybe to make it sound archaic}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.10,0:02:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, the monks at the temple \Nsaid you'd gone to the beach.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.79,0:02:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.58,0:02:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but it's very nice here.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.11,0:02:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord asked me to find you.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.10,0:03:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not busy, \Nhe'd like you to play for him.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.17,0:03:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not busy right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.12,0:03:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful! My lord is entertaining \Na guest from Akashi.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.12,0:03:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He heard about your skill\N with the biwa,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.27,0:03:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so now he's dying to hear it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.74,0:03:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.15,0:03:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... let's go to your master.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.52,0:03:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me your hand.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.97,0:03:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.23,0:03:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.54,0:03:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.82,0:03:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You almost stepped on a crab.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.60,0:03:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A Heike crab?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.06,0:03:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They say the crabs were once possessed
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.67,0:03:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,by the spirits of Heike \Nwho died here at Dan-no-Ura.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.61,0:03:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, the crab's shell holds the image of a human face.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.57,0:03:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My word, that stuff is creepy.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.49,0:03:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you like to hear?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.58,0:03:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to hear {\i1}The Battle of Dan-no-Ura{\i0}, of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.93,0:03:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.31,0:04:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi's rendition of that song \Nis magnificent.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.09,0:04:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please let us hear it, Hoichi-san.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.61,0:04:20.61,Song,,0,0,0,,The soldiers of the Genji boarded the Heike boats
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.61,0:04:24.82,Song,,0,0,0,,There they took up swords {supposedly https://guignardbiwa.com/en/library/dannoura/ but the language is too old so believing the officials}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.83,0:04:33.93,Song,,0,0,0,,And cut the Heike down
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.54,0:04:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.04,0:04:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Priest, are you going out?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.13,0:04:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:42.33,0:04:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to Sugino village.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.15,0:04:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yasuke-san, hasn't the chief priest returned yet?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.77,0:05:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't be back until tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.64,0:05:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.05,0:05:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.98,0:05:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I'm sorry, but I can't see.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.89,0:05:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.39,0:05:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.54,0:06:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I am staying near this temple.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.73,0:06:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I have need of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.07,0:06:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.01,0:06:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,My lady is a noble ruler \Nwho leads a great retinue of vassals. {??? his archaic speech is beyond me}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.73,0:06:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They are staying in this area.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.92,0:06:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We've come to see \Nthe battlefield of Dan-no-Ura,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.98,0:06:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and we heard that you excel\N at recounting the details of the battle.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.13,0:06:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you bring your biwa and sing the story for us?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.57,0:06:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.89,0:06:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me now.\N I will take you to my lady.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.36,0:07:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Open the gates!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.57,0:07:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, take my hand.\N There's a staircase.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.02,0:07:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea there was a mansion so close to the temple.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.61,0:07:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but please, try to be as quiet as possible while you're here.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.62,0:08:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.47,0:08:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We have arrived.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.73,0:08:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Minstrel Hoichi, we ask that you perform {\i1}The Tale of the Heike{\i0} on your biwa.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.14,0:08:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly.{As you wish?}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.75,0:08:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire tale is too long to tell.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.37,0:08:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Which chapter do you want first?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.76,0:08:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Play for us "The Battle of Dan-no-Ura."
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.19,0:08:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a particularly tragic tale.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.00,0:09:07.86,Song,,0,0,0,,Elsewhere {??? same, no clue about the text of this song}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.78,0:09:18.45,Song,,0,0,0,,The Genpei war continued to rage
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.47,0:09:25.45,Song,,0,0,0,,Throughout the realm
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.29,0:09:46.58,Song,,0,0,0,,The winds of spring
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.57,0:09:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You truly are a master of the biwa.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.80,0:10:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My lady was greatly pleased.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.48,0:10:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We have returned.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.76,0:10:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.50,0:10:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, tell no one of this visit\N and what happened tonight.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.05,0:10:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,My lady's presence here\N must remain a secret.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.87,0:10:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.82,0:10:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I will return tomorrow at the same time.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.05,0:11:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still asleep?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.43,0:11:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi-san. Hoichi-san!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.48,0:11:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.42,0:11:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you feeling unwell?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.68,0:11:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I just overslept.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.40,0:11:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, is that all? \NThe sun's already in the west.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.09,0:11:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that late?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.49,0:11:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi, will you come with me once more?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.29,0:11:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Such fine biwa playing!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.69,0:12:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We are deeply pleased with your skill\N these past two nights.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.19,0:12:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We will grant you a reward\N that matches your skills.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.13,0:12:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi-san!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.97,0:12:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi-san!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.32,0:12:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi-san, the chief priest wants you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.85,0:12:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not mad, just worried.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.18,0:12:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're blind. You can't go wandering around alone at night.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.35,0:12:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Chief Priest, \Nbut there's something I must do,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.55,0:12:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can only do it in the late evening.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.58,0:12:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If Hoichi leaves the temple again tonight,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.48,0:13:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to find out where he's going.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.47,0:13:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.59,0:13:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a sense of foreboding \Nthat I can't do anything about.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.71,0:13:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Tch. It's getting pretty dark.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.95,0:13:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get a lantern.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.13,0:13:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.85,0:13:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi, are you prepared?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.57,0:13:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.58,0:13:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There he goes!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.59,0:13:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What's taking Chinnen so long? {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.16,0:13:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up. Hoichi-san just left.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.26,0:13:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You worry too much.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.41,0:13:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't have gone far so soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.23,0:14:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He went out the back gate.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.34,0:14:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd. \NThis is the only road to town.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.91,0:14:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He's faster than I thought.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.12,0:14:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have to find him.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.79,0:14:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:23.51,0:14:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's definitely not right.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.48,0:14:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We should have caught up already.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.89,0:14:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he went to the beach?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.35,0:14:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But that road winds\N through the graveyard.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.14,0:14:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too difficult for him.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.93,0:14:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a moth.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.39,0:14:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It scared me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.95,0:14:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's check the beach.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.77,0:14:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the graveyard?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.88,0:14:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the only way.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.86,0:14:57.66,Song,,0,0,0,,And the Genji pressed them toward the beach
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.66,0:15:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you hear that?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.88,0:15:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.21,0:15:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds like a biwa.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.37,0:15:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.77,0:15:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from the graveyard!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.39,0:15:20.44,Song,,0,0,0,,All the arrowheads lay in wait
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.48,0:15:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.30,0:15:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the Heike graveyard.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.84,0:15:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He's under a spell!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.79,0:15:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi-san! Hoichi-san!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.19,0:15:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back to the temple!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.80,0:15:47.96,Song,,0,0,0,,Striking down the rowers {船手漕手も討ち果たされ}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.51,0:15:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use. He can't hear me.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.97,0:15:59.98,Song,,0,0,0,,Directionless, the Heike ships sank to the bottom {行方も知らず平家の船あるいは沈み}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.98,0:16:05.89,Song,,0,0,0,,Or they floated adrift {あるいは漂い}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.89,0:16:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let them fool you, Hoichi-san!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.85,0:16:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.98,0:16:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't be so impolite.\NWe're in front of nobility!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.99,0:16:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's go back now.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.14,0:16:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The chief priest is worried about you.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.92,0:16:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be quiet.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.60,0:16:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,W-We have to get out of here!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.42,0:16:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor soul. You're treading\N on extremely thin ice now. {lit: is living through very dangerous experience}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.39,0:16:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Your skill with the biwa has led you to the brink of doom.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.92,0:16:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I never guessed that\N I was playing for ghosts.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.19,0:16:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Their spirits are disturbed now.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.79,0:17:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, you, a mortal, have already answered their call once.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.42,0:17:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's worse, you promised to play \Nfor them seven nights in a row.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.76,0:17:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll come for you again tonight.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.77,0:17:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do, Chief Priest?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.88,0:17:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go again, \Nthey'll tear you limb from limb.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.35,0:17:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, we can still save you.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:26.14,0:17:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This evening, you'll go with them as usual, but before that,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:29.45,0:17:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll paint sutras over your entire body.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.12,0:17:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That should protect you.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.45,0:18:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm done.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.20,0:18:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait on the porch tonight.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.19,0:18:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Your guide will come for you again.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.27,0:18:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But no matter what happens, \Nyou must not answer him.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.16,0:18:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.37,0:18:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't even move.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.99,0:18:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you move even slightly\N or make the smallest sound,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.33,0:18:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll find you.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.57,0:18:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't even be able to call for help.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.36,0:18:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.68,0:18:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you do exactly as I've told you,\N the danger will pass.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.59,0:18:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have nothing to fear henceforth.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:50.80,0:18:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.80,0:19:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be in the kitchen all night, \Nso if you need me, just call{\fscx300}-
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.27,0:19:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry, you can't.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.08,0:19:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.28,0:19:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.29,0:19:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.09,0:19:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.15,0:20:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.25,0:20:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's his biwa.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.72,0:20:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Only two ears!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.49,0:20:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The biwa player has lost his mouth and cannot answer me.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.84,0:20:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Only his ears remain.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.25,0:20:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to take these ears\N back to my mistress
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.28,0:20:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as proof that I searched\N as hard as I could.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.10,0:21:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all my fault. The poor soul.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.87,0:21:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to write sutras on his ears.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.11,0:21:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was unforgivable.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:25.22,0:21:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't blame yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.71,0:21:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At least I'm free of the danger now.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:30.76,0:21:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true, so cheer up.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.52,0:21:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll never come for you again.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.99,0:22:09.26,Song,,0,0,0,,The bell of the Gion temple
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.34,0:22:09.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Hoichi received good care,\N and his wounds soon healed.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.03,0:22:15.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Tales of this strange incident reached far and wide.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:15.39,0:22:19.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Hoichi the Earless became famous, \Nand his story is remembered to this day. {see Wikipedia, Hoichi the Earless}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.83,0:22:37.69,Song,,0,0,0,,I write a letter to my loved one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.39,0:22:44.61,Song,,0,0,0,,I write and tear it, tear it, and write again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.61,0:22:51.16,Song,,0,0,0,,I throw the rolled up paper at the window
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.16,0:22:58.33,Song,,0,0,0,,It's raining outside, just like the tears on my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.44,0:23:06.21,Song,,0,0,0,,Life is a sea, youth is a boat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.21,0:23:13.28,Song,,0,0,0,,My love, please come and save me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.28,0:23:15.70,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.59,0:23:18.81,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.45,0:23:26.96,Song,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm sinking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.96,0:23:36.38,Song,,0,0,0,,Not a single star in sight, in the sea of ​​sadness
